{"build_type":"library","description":"Explicit iterative driver of the runtime linker's transitive dependency-closure load, replacing the former native mutual recursion (import-named-object <-> import-relocation-targets) that overflowed the 8 MiB stack on deep dependency chains. The thread-local LIFO worklist lives entirely inside its buffer argument (buf[0]=top, buf[1]=cap, buf[2..]=pending names), so only the buffer pointer is threaded (register ABI: <=4 args) and each loader thread owns its walk with no cross-thread state beyond the shared g_ld_map. One step: read top from buf[0]; if zero, return; else pop the top name and decrement buf[0]; if the name is already in g_ld_map skip it (guard-on-pop keeps the queue bounded by dependency edges); otherwise load the object (resolve, decode, copy code into g_ld_region at g_ld_cursor, record map[name]=base, stamp __base, append to g_ld_loaded), push its relocation targets, and tail-recurse (compiled to a jmp-back loop, O(1) native stack). Relocation patching stays the separate later pass patch-every-loaded-object-relocation, so load order does not affect correctness.","module_name":"import-dependency-closure-worklist-iteration","package_name":"import-dependency-closure-worklist-iteration","function_definitions":{"import-dependency-closure-worklist-iteration":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"buf","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"fifteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_tar